# CozyArcade.games - Site Design Document

Version 1.0 | November 2024

## Executive Summary

CozyArcade.games aims to become a premier destination for web-based gaming, offering a curated collection of games in a welcoming, user-friendly environment. The platform will initially focus on delivering a robust, scalable infrastructure that can accommodate various game types while providing an exceptional user experience.

## Core Values

- **Cozy First**: Create a warm, inviting space that feels like a digital arcade living room
- **Universal Access**: Games that work across devices with minimal friction
- **Performance**: Fast loading times and smooth gameplay
- **Community**: Foster a friendly, engaged gaming community
- **Quality Over Quantity**: Curated game selection over vast libraries

## Technical Architecture

### Frontend

- **Framework**: Next.js with React 18
  - Server-side rendering for optimal performance
  - Static generation for content pages
  - API routes for dynamic functionality
- **Styling**:
  - Tailwind CSS for utility-first styling
  - CSS Modules for component-specific styles
  - CSS Variables for theming
- **State Management**:
  - React Context for app-wide state
  - React Query for API data management
- **Game Integration**:
  - Isolated iframes for third-party games
  - Custom Web Components for native games
  - WebGL/Canvas contexts for graphics-intensive games

### Backend

- **API**: Node.js with Express
- **Database**: PostgreSQL
  - User profiles and authentication
  - Game metadata and statistics
  - Leaderboards and achievements
- **Cache Layer**: Redis
  - Session management
  - Real-time features
  - Performance optimization

Infrastructure
Hosting: Netlify
Automatic deployments from Git
Branch deployments for testing
Built-in CI/CD pipeline
Edge functions for serverless computing
Forms handling for user feedback
Split testing capabilities
Built-in CDN
SSL certificate management
Deploy previews for pull requests
Asset Storage: AWS S3
Analytics: Plausible Analytics (Privacy-focused)

## Site Structure

### Core Pages

1. **Home Page** (`/`)

   - Featured games carousel
   - Popular games grid
   - Latest additions
   - Community highlights
   - Quick-play section

2. **Game Page** (`/games/:slug`)

   - Game container
   - Description and controls
   - Leaderboard
   - Related games
   - Comments section

3. **Categories** (`/categories`)

   - Organized game collections
   - Filtering system
   - Search functionality

4. **Profile** (`/profile`)

   - Game history
   - Achievements
   - Favorites
   - Settings

5. **Community** (`/community`)
   - Forums
   - Leaderboards
   - News and updates
   - Events

### Features & Components

#### Navigation

- Persistent header with logo and main nav
- Quick game search
- User menu
- Mobile-responsive hamburger menu

#### Game Browser

- Advanced filtering system
- Sort by popularity/date/rating
- Grid/list view toggle
- Infinite scroll with lazy loading

#### Game Player

- Responsive container
- Fullscreen support
- Control customization
- Performance monitoring

#### User Features

- Authentication system
- Game progress saving
- Cross-device synchronization
- Social features

## Visual Design

Color Palette
Primary: #7E57C2 (Rich Purple)
Used for primary actions and key UI elements
Creates sense of imagination and creativity
Perfect for branded elements
High visibility without being aggressive
Secondary: #2C3E50 (Deep Blue-Gray)
Container backgrounds
Secondary UI elements
Content area backgrounds
Provides depth and sophistication
Accent: #FF916B (Soft Coral)
Call-to-action buttons
Highlighting important elements
Progress indicators
Brings warmth to the interface
Background: #1A1D21 (Soft Charcoal)
Main background color
Dark mode default
Reduces eye strain
Makes content pop
Text: #F0F4F8 (Cool White)
Primary text color
UI element outlines
Icons and symbols
Optimal readability
Supporting Accent: #64FFDA (Mint)
Success states
Achievement indicators
Progress completion
Secondary highlights
Color Usage Guidelines
Interactive Elements
Primary buttons: Rich Purple (#7E57C2)
Secondary buttons: Deep Blue-Gray (#2C3E50)
Hover states: Lighten by 10%
Active states: Darken by 10%
Text Hierarchy
Primary text: Cool White (#F0F4F8)
Secondary text: Cool White at 80% opacity
Disabled text: Cool White at 40% opacity
Links: Mint (#64FFDA)
Status Indicators
Success: Mint (#64FFDA)
Warning: Soft Coral (#FF916B)
Error: Darker shade of Soft Coral
Info: Rich Purple (#7E57C2)
Containers
Primary containers: Deep Blue-Gray (#2C3E50)
Secondary containers: Soft Charcoal (#1A1D21)
Card backgrounds: Deep Blue-Gray at 60% opacity
Modal overlays: Soft Charcoal at 80% opacity

### Typography

- Headings: Poppins (Bold, Semi-bold)
- Body: Inter (Regular, Medium)
- Game Titles: Space Grotesk (Medium)

### Design Elements

- Soft shadows
- Rounded corners (12px)
- Subtle gradients
- Micro-animations
- Loading states
- Dark mode by default

## Monetization Strategy

### Phase 1: Foundation

- Focus on user acquisition
- Optional donations
- Basic advertisement integration

### Phase 2: Revenue Streams

- Premium game partnerships
- Non-intrusive advertisements
- Premium memberships
  - Ad-free experience
  - Exclusive games
  - Early access

### Phase 3: Expansion

- Developer platform
- Revenue sharing
- Sponsored tournaments
- Virtual currency system

## Performance Targets

- Core Web Vitals
  - LCP: < 2.5s
  - FID: < 100ms
  - CLS: < 0.1
- Page Load: < 3s
- Time to Interactive: < 3.5s
- Performance Score: > 90

## Security Measures

- HTTPS enforcement
- Content Security Policy
- Rate limiting
- DDOS protection
- Regular security audits
- Data encryption
- Secure authentication

## Launch Roadmap

### MVP (Month 1-2)

- Basic site structure
- Authentication system
- Game embedding system
- Initial game collection (5-10 games)
- Basic profile system

### Phase 2 (Month 3-4)

- Enhanced game browser
- Social features
- Achievement system
- Basic monetization
- Performance optimization

### Phase 3 (Month 5-6)

- Community features
- Advanced game integration
- Premium features
- Mobile optimization
- Analytics integration

